"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Refactor `CalculateTokenUsage` to accept `[]byte` and use canonical interface\n\n## Context\n\n`TokenCalculator.CalculateTokenUsage` currently takes a file path (`sessionRef string`) and each agent reads the file internally. Meanwhile, the condensation code in the strategy package has its own `calculateTokenUsage` helper that dispatches by `agentType` to package-level functions, bypassing the interface entirely. This refactoring:\n\n1. Changes the interface to accept `data []byte` so callers that already have bytes (condensation) don't need file I/O\n2. Makes the strategy's helper use the canonical `TokenCalculator` interface via `agent.GetByAgentType`\n\n## Changes\n\n### 1. Interface signature (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/agent.go:169`)\n\n```go\n// Before\nCalculateTokenUsage(sessionRef string, fromOffset int) (*TokenUsage, error)\n// After\nCalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*TokenUsage, error)\n```\n\n### 2. Claude Code implementation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/lifecycle.go:131-138`)\n\nReplace file-based delegation with bytes-based parsing:\n```go\nfunc (c *ClaudeCodeAgent) CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*agent.TokenUsage, error) {\n    lines, err := transcript.ParseFromBytes(data)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse transcript: %w\", err)\n    }\n    if fromOffset > 0 && fromOffset < len(lines) {\n        lines = lines[fromOffset:]\n    }\n    return CalculateTokenUsage(lines), nil\n}\n```\n\nNote: This does NOT include subagent tokens. The subagent-aware path is handled separately by `SubagentAwareExtractor.CalculateTotalTokenUsage` which lifecycle.go already prefers. That interface is not changed.\n\n### 3. Gemini CLI implementation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/lifecycle.go:99-102`)\n\nDelegate to the existing bytes-based package-level function:\n```go\nfunc (g *GeminiCLIAgent) CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*agent.TokenUsage, error) {\n    return CalculateTokenUsage(data, fromOffset), nil\n}\n```\n\n(The package-level `geminicli.CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, startMessageIndex int)` already accepts bytes.)\n\n### 4. OpenCode implementation (`cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/transcript.go:295-322`)\n\nDelegate to the existing `CalculateTokenUsageFromBytes`:\n```go\nfunc (a *OpenCodeAgent) CalculateTokenUsage(data []byte, fromOffset int) (*agent.TokenUsage, error) {\n    return CalculateTokenUsageFromBytes(data, fromOffset), nil\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Lifecycle caller (`cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go:357-365`)\n\nPass `transcriptData` (already loaded at line 193) instead of `transcriptRef`:\n```go\nusage, tokenErr := calculator.CalculateTokenUsage(transcriptData, transcriptLinesAtStart)\n```\n\n### 6. Condensation helper (`cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:589-627`)\n\nReplace the switch-dispatch with the canonical interface:\n```go\nfunc calculateTokenUsage(agentType agent.AgentType, data []byte, startOffset int) *agent.TokenUsage {\n    if len(data) == 0 {\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\n    }\n    ag, err := agent.GetByAgentType(agentType)\n    if err != nil {\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\n    }\n    calculator, ok := ag.(agent.TokenCalculator)\n    if !ok {\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\n    }\n    usage, err := calculator.CalculateTokenUsage(data, startOffset)\n    if err != nil {\n        return &agent.TokenUsage{}\n    }\n    return usage\n}\n```\n\nThis removes the direct calls to `claudecode.CalculateTokenUsage`, `geminicli.CalculateTokenUsage`, and `opencode.CalculateTokenUsageFromBytes` from condensation. The `transcript` import for `ParseFromBytes` also moves out (it's now inside the Claude Code agent method). The agent sub-package imports (`claudecode`, `geminicli`, `opencode`) remain needed for other functions in the file.\n\n### 7. Update tests\n\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/opencode/transcript_test.go`**: Update `TestCalculateTokenUsage`, `TestCalculateTokenUsage_FromOffset`, and `TestCalculateTokenUsage_NonexistentFile` to pass `[]byte` instead of file paths\n- **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/claudecode/transcript_test.go`** and **`cmd/entire/cli/agent/geminicli/transcript_test.go`**: Package-level function tests don't change (they already test the core logic). No new method-level tests needed since the methods are thin wrappers.\n\n## Not changed\n\n- `SubagentAwareExtractor.CalculateTotalTokenUsage` - still file-path-based (needs to discover and read subagent files from disk)\n- `claudecode.CalculateTokenUsageFromFile` / `claudecode.CalculateTotalTokenUsage` - kept for the `SubagentAwareExtractor` path\n- `geminicli.CalculateTokenUsageFromFile` - kept as convenience helper\n- Package-level `CalculateTokenUsage` functions in each agent - kept as the core logic\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\nmise run fmt && mise run lint && mise run test:ci\n```\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/robin/.claude/projects/-Users-robin-Developer-cli/b1f148f7-fe06-42ab-bda9-a8ab977397db.jsonl\n\n---\n\nin manual_commit_condensation.go, if the agent does not implement agent.TokenCalculator we should return nil, not &agent.TokenUsage{}\n\n---\n\nhow do the new changes affect subagent token usage calculation, especially for claude?\n\n---\n\ncan we refactor away SubagentAwareExtractor.CalculateTotalTokenUsage and instead just rely on using ExtractAllModifiedFiles.ExtractAllModifiedFiles to get the file content and then feeding it to TokenCalculator.CalculateTokenUsage?"